00:00:02.680 --> 00:00:04.100
Welcome to instant Cooking

00:00:04.820 --> 00:00:05.940
Today I am making

00:00:06.780 --> 00:00:09.880
Little spicy and very tasty Dal Kolhapuri

00:00:10.280 --> 00:00:15.420
for this we need soaked bengal gram, I have soaked it for an hour

00:00:15.720 --> 00:00:20.280
Red Chilly powder, Turmeric Powder, Ginger &amp; garlic

00:00:21.300 --> 00:00:23.420
sliced onion, Salt

00:00:24.240 --> 00:00:28.080
Coriander leaves, Tomato, Cumin &amp; coriander seed powder

00:00:28.300 --> 00:00:35.500
Some whole spices Star Anise, Green Cardamom, Cloves, Black pepper, Bay leaf &amp; Cinnamon.

00:00:35.680 --> 00:00:36.740
So, firstly

00:00:38.520 --> 00:00:39.460
In a pan

00:00:40.480 --> 00:00:43.140
Add 2-3 tsp of refined oil

00:00:48.580 --> 00:00:51.680
And on very low flame add whole spices

00:00:52.580 --> 00:00:53.960
3-4 cloves

00:00:56.760 --> 00:00:58.820
5-7 black pepper

00:01:00.400 --> 00:01:03.400
Approximately 1 inch of Cinnamon

00:01:04.200 --> 00:01:06.920
A small piece of Star Anise

00:01:07.760 --> 00:01:09.100
2 green Cardamom

00:01:10.080 --> 00:01:12.440
and 1 bay leaf. Mix it

00:01:12.460 --> 00:01:17.300
So on very low flame cook the whole spices for 40 -50 seconds

00:01:18.540 --> 00:01:22.760
So, while our whole spices is cooking , will make our masala

00:01:22.920 --> 00:01:27.680
For this take a grinder add 1 small piece of bay leaf

00:01:27.860 --> 00:01:36.700
1/2 inch of cinnamon, 3-4 cloves, 10 black pepper, 1 green cardamom, 1 medium size sliced onion

00:01:39.200 --> 00:01:40.480
10 cloves of garlic

00:01:43.040 --> 00:01:45.380
And 1/2 inch of ginger

00:01:47.360 --> 00:01:52.460
Now add the dry masala, 1 tsp of coriander &amp; cumin seed powder

00:01:52.780 --> 00:01:55.020
1/2 tsp of Turmeric Powder

00:01:58.040 --> 00:02:01.740
1 tsp of red chilly powder

00:02:02.240 --> 00:02:03.520
add little water

00:02:04.480 --> 00:02:06.400
And grind it to a fine paste

00:02:09.120 --> 00:02:13.420
So, our masala is ready &amp; our whole spices are also cooked

00:02:13.800 --> 00:02:19.680
So, I will add 3 medium size sliced onion, approximately 200 gm of chopped onion

00:02:20.380 --> 00:02:22.380
Now you can increase the flame

00:02:22.480 --> 00:02:25.460
Mix it and cook the onion till brown

00:02:25.700 --> 00:02:28.860
To cook onion salt, you can add a pinch of salt

00:02:29.200 --> 00:02:35.400
Mix it you have to cook onion till golden brown, It will take 2-3 minutes

00:02:35.600 --> 00:02:38.520
Now, you can see our onion is golden brown

00:02:38.700 --> 00:02:41.340
So, we will add the masala which we have just made

00:02:43.060 --> 00:02:44.380
Now , mix it well

00:02:46.580 --> 00:02:49.080
And cook for another 2-3 minutes

00:02:49.400 --> 00:02:52.060
We have to cook masala on medium flame

00:02:52.240 --> 00:02:54.000
Don't cook it on high flame

00:02:54.500 --> 00:02:56.540
So, the masala cook properly

00:02:56.780 --> 00:03:00.600
So, on medium flame cook it for 2-3 minutes

00:03:01.200 --> 00:03:03.640
And cook this masala till oil separates

00:03:04.360 --> 00:03:09.480
Now, you can see our masala is properly cooked, oil is separated

00:03:10.360 --> 00:03:16.140
So, now I will add approximately 200 gm of soaked Bengal Gram.

00:03:17.580 --> 00:03:22.160
Mix it well &amp; cook it for 1-2 minutes

00:03:22.720 --> 00:03:25.600
So, our bengal gram is cooking for 2 minutes

00:03:26.080 --> 00:03:29.460
Now, i will take medium size tomato

00:03:29.840 --> 00:03:33.020
And grind them &amp; make fresh tomato puree

00:03:36.020 --> 00:03:39.980
And now we will add the fresh tomato puree into the dal

00:03:40.500 --> 00:03:41.480
Mix it well

00:03:43.400 --> 00:03:47.000
And cook till extra moisture of tomato will evaporate

00:03:47.000 --> 00:03:50.720
It will take around 2 minutes, now add salt to taste

00:03:52.080 --> 00:03:54.540
Mix it and cook it 2 minutes

00:03:55.000 --> 00:03:57.500
Stir continousley on high flame

00:03:57.960 --> 00:04:01.280
Now, add around 300 ml of water

00:04:02.820 --> 00:04:03.760
Mix it well

00:04:04.400 --> 00:04:05.520
Keep stirring

00:04:06.300 --> 00:04:07.660
and bring it to a boil

00:04:07.860 --> 00:04:13.440
Now, take a pressure cooked and transfer this dal kolhapuri in pressure cooker

00:04:16.060 --> 00:04:20.780
And now pressure cook for 3 whistle around 5-7 minutes

00:04:21.760 --> 00:04:25.940
and then we will serve it , garnish it with coriander leaves

00:04:25.940 --> 00:04:31.920
And your, little lengthy but very tasty, very delicious Dal Kplhapuri is ready.

